<div class="panel-heading">
<h4 class="panel-title"><a href="#collapse1" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion">Personal Directors&rsquo; and Officers&rsquo; Liability Insurance</a></h4>
</div>
<div id="collapse1" class="panel-collapse collapse">
<div class="panel-body">
<p><strong>Personal Directors&rsquo; and Officers&rsquo; Liability Insurance <br /></strong> <em>Underwritten by Allianz General Insurance Malaysia Berhad</em></p>
<p><strong>What is this product for?</strong> <br />Directors and Officers Liability insurance is designed to protect non-executive directors and officers of companies against personal liability that they might incur in respect of amounts which they are liable for, in respect of claims made against them arising out of the performance of their duties.</p>
<p>Many company directors worry that their company does not buy or renew D&amp;O Liability insurance, that the coverage is not adequate, or that the policy may not be activated to protect them when the need arises.</p>
<p><strong>Who needs Personal D&amp;O Insurance?</strong> <br />It is not only full-time company directors who will benefit from the introduction of Personal D&amp;O Insurance. Accountants, lawyers, and other professional who accept temporary or permanent positions on the boards of their client companies have an obvious need for such a portable, personal cover. Companies that are trying to attract top talent to their board may also offer a Personal D&amp;O Insurance policy as an extra benefit. The key benefit of this policy is its inherent flexibility.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Table of Coverage</strong></p>
<table class="table-bordered table-condensed">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
