<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>FAQs</strong></p>
<ol start="1">
<li><strong>Will the premiums increase as my age increases?</strong> <br /><em>Yes. The premium payable will depend on your attained age which shall be the age at the nearest birthday at each policy anniversary.</em></li>
</ol>
<ol start="2">
<ol start="2">
<li><strong>Are the premiums for the product guaranteed?</strong> <br /><em>The premiums for this plan is not guaranteed and the insurance company reserves the right to revise the premium by giving the policyholders 30 days written notice to the next policy anniversary. </em></li>
</ol>
</ol>
<p><em>Factors contributing to the increase in premiums are age specific and plan specific, claims experience, medical inflation, etc.</em></p>
<ol start="3">
<li><strong>Are the premiums paid or this product eligible for income tax relief? </strong> <br />Yes, the premiums paid for this plan may qualify you for a personal tax relief of up to RM 3,000 for medical and education insurance, subject to the final decision of the Inland Revenue Board of Malaysiabr</li>
</ol>
<ol start="4">
<li><strong>What are the major exclusions for this product?</strong> <br />No benefit shall be payable for any of the following services, products or conditions or injuries resulting from:</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>Pre-existing conditions prior to the inception (the first time or whenever there is a break of cover) of the insurance cover, whichever is later;</li>
<li>Specified illnesses below that occurs within the first hundred and twenty (120) days of cover:</li>
<li>Hypertension, diabetes mellitus and Cardiovascular disease;
<ul>
<li>All tumours, cancers, cysts, nodules, polyps, stones of the urinary system and biliary system; &bull; All ear, nose (including sinuses) and throat conditions;</li>
<li>Hernias, haemorrhoids, fistulae, hydrocele, varicocele;</li>
<li>Endometriosis including disease of the Reproduction system;</li>
<li>Vertebro-spinal disorders (including disc) and knee conditions;</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Illness or disease occurring within the first thirty (30) days from the Effective Date or Date of Reinstatement, whichever is later;</li>
<li>Cosmetic surgery or treatment, or treatment of their complications (inclusive of double eyelids, acne, keloids etc) except as necessitated by accidental injuries;</li>
<li>Care and treatment that is experimental, investigative and not according to accepted professional standards and care that is not medically necessary;</li>
<li>Treatment for injuries sustained while committing a crime or felony, or while under the influence of alcohol, narcotics, or mind-altering substance or injuries which are self-inflicted while sane or insane.</li>
<li>Investigation and treatment relating to pregnancy including childbirth and all complications arising therefrom except for miscarriage due to motor vehicle accident, subject to its limitations;</li>
<li>Treatment, therapy or surgical operation for congenital or hereditary diseases, deformities and disabilities and any medical or surgical complication arising therefrom;</li>
<li>Any medical treatment received outside Malaysia, apart from Singapore and Brunei, if the Insured resides or travels outside Malaysia for more than ninety (90) consecutive days. <br /><em>Note: This list is non-exhaustive. Please refer to the policy contract for the full list of exclusions under this Policy</em></li>
</ul>
<ol start="5">
<li><strong>Is there any amount that I have to pay upon discharge?</strong> <br />Depending on the plan and deductible option chosen, you will have to bear the self-insured deductible amount (if any), and also the items which are not covered by the policy. The self-insured deductible amount indicated is based on the attained age of the Insured at the point of claim.</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel panel-default">
<div class="panel-heading">
<h4 class="panel-title"><a href="#collapse5" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion">General FAQs</a></h4>
</div>
<div id="collapse5" class="panel-collapse collapse">
<div class="panel-body">
<p><strong>General FAQs</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>I would like to purchase one of these insurance products, what do I do? <br /></strong>Our strategic partner, Sterling Insurance Brokers will be managing all the insurance requirements for ICDM Protect. Once you fill up the form at the bottom of the page, Sterling will get in touch with you promptly regarding the possible options. <br /><br />Alternatively, you may get in touch with them at <a href="mailto:icdm@sterlinggroup.com.my">icdm@sterlinggroup.com.my</a> or get in touch with Ili Elina/Ahmad Fauzan Sterling at +603-2938 6888</li>
</ol>
<ol start="2">
<li><strong>Can I buy any of these products if I am not a member of ICDM ? <br /></strong>Unfortunately not. These products are only made available to ICDM members . A Health Maximiser and Personal D&amp;O are not available for anyone else to purchase directly, and Smarthome and the Personal Accident cover are given at highly competitive rates.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="3">
<li><strong>What happens to my purchased insurance(s) if I am no longer an ICDM member?</strong> <br />Purchased insurance must be renewed with a valid ICDM membership to continuously enjoy the competitive premium and comprehensive coverage ICDM and Sterling have provided. In the event your ICDM membership is discontinued, for any reason, you may renew the insurance products at a different premium, as may be determined by Sterling.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="4">
<li><strong>How do I make a claim? What if my details were to change? What about any other questions I may have? <br /></strong>All queries regarding insurance transactions/claims and changes in details are to be referred to ICDM&rsquo;s strategic partner, Sterling Insurance Brokers, who will advise you accordingly.</li>
</ol>
<ol start="5">
<li><strong>Can I cancel my policy? <br /></strong>You may terminate your policy by giving written notice to Sterling Insurance Brokers. Termination shall become effective on the date the notice is received or on the date specified in such notice whichever is the later. Refund of premium, however, is subject to the terms and conditions stipulated in the Policy (to be referred to each of the policy documents).</li>
</ol>
<ol start="6">
<li><strong>What do I need to do if there are changes to my contact/personal details? <br /></strong>It is important that you inform us of any changes in your contact and personal details to ensure that all correspondence reach you timely manner.</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
